# A comment inside an otherwise empty struct body is attached to the
# StructLit itself (Position > 0). It must be rendered inside the
# braces, not after them. Two layouts are possible and each is
# preserved:
#
#   - own-line: `{\n\t// c\n}` - the comment stands on its own line
#     between the braces.
#   - open-line: `{ // c\n}` - the comment trails the opener on the
#     same line, separated by a single space.
#
# The CUE parser distinguishes them via the comment's Slash RelPos:
# Newline (or NewSection) for the own-line shape, Blank for the
# open-line shape. (The parser also sets cg.Line=true alongside Blank,
# but the formatter treats Slash.RelPos as the source of truth - see
# commentSep - and Line is just a redundant projection of RelPos=Blank.)
# The important invariant is that the comment never escapes to a
# trailing position on the surrounding field, regardless of layout.
#
# In the norelpos case stripRelPos clears both knobs, so the open-
# line shape is no longer distinguishable from the own-line shape:
# both render with the comment on its own line.
-- in.cue --
a: {
	// own-line interior
}

b: { // open-line interior
}
-- out/relpos --
a: {
	// own-line interior
}

b: { // open-line interior
}
-- out/norelpos --
a: {
	// own-line interior
}
b: {
	// open-line interior
}
